    <main>
      <h2>Charharshanbe Suri</h2>
      
      <div class="content">
      <p>A voice too afraid to speak<br>
For generations caught soundless between<br>
The torrents of raging zealotry<br>
	Surging in ambient industrial noise
      </p>
      
      <p>
Thought trapped between the screeching<br>
Of rusted gears and entitled boys<br>
Fist and feet ready to stamp out the waver<br>
In any softness, creeping slowly
      </p>

      <p>
Under the surface, arrhythmic<br>
Murmurs of an unsteady heart<br>
Unready to take the lead in life<br>
Except in scenes; a voice curtailed
      </p>

      <p>
By double-stitched seams, now hogging<br>
And bursting as the weight of a well<br>
Tailored childhood comes tumbling out<br>
The communal wail of people long
      </p>

      <p>
Oppressed, ready to uprise the many<br>
Shouts louder than a football stadium<br>
When the Dockers play the Eagles and<br>
My voice is one of theirs, now
      </p>

      <p>
A late entrance to the Millennial change<br>
And I am no longer afraid.
      </p>

      <p>
I tire of being fucked on the pedestal<br>
Of propriety and desulted in temples<br>
Of malicious mock modesty; knock down<br>
The tables of moneylenders and tear down
      </p>

      <p>
The idols in perverse places of power,<br>
Bloated and tired, the clichés are<br>
Ready to go my hair flows free now,<br>
Longing to join the wind
      </p>

      <p>
Of other women, singing together,<br>
Empowered only by themselves,<br>
The billions of distinct songs, sounds,<br>
And rhythms, multitudinous,
      </p>

      <p>
All harmonizing together, a beautiful<br>
Crystal individuality that will scratch<br>
Through the old monoliths and keep<br>
Growing and changing, echoing through
      </p>

      <p>
The years, the chant<br>
زن زندگی آزادی<br>
Still rolling through my ears<br>
And off my tongue, a few notes
      </p>

      <p>
In the deafening choir where<br>
My voice radiates like a solar flare<br>
But if you listen, it still trembles<br>
To the murmurs of my heart,
      </p>

      <p>
And I assert a continued<br>
Softness will quietly let<br>
The world hear that I still<br>
Hurt just the same, through
      </p>

      <p>
A trembled whisper my blood<br>
Spills red on the page
      </p>


      <p>زردی من از تو سرخی تو از من</p>
      
      <p>
	As I jump over the pains of the old<br>
Year, may the flames of the new<br>
Burn brightly under my feet and<br>
	Make me sing a while more.
      </p>
      </div>
      
